<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="cure-n">cure <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kjʊə(r)/    美 /kjʊr/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>治疗；痊愈：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Prevention is better than cure.
预防胜于治疗。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His complete cure can’t be expected.
他完全恢复健康遥不可期。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>疗法；药物：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>One day scientists will find a <strong>cure for</strong> AIDS.
总有一天科学家会找到治疗艾滋病的方法。</p><footer>人教⑥ – 3</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>对策：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>cure for</strong> rising prices
抑制物价上涨的对策</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Empathy can be a <strong>cure for</strong> loneliness, sadness, anxiety, and fear.
同情是应付孤独、悲伤、焦虑和恐惧的对策。</p></div></div>